subSubSection.paragraph:
Dorsal colouration (
Fig. 38a
): pronotum almost completely black, except for yellow lateral sides; elytra testaceous, with a characteristic dark pattern: cross-like, with two little pale spots inside and two transverse spurs reaching the humerus. This pattern rather constant, althought dark colouration in some speciemens more or less extended.
